==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Boarder
<hw>Board"er</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>One who
has food statedly at another's table, or meals and lodgings in his
house, for pay, or compensation of any kind.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Naut.)</fld> <def>One who boards a ship; one
selected to board an enemy's ship.</def> <rj><au>Totten.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Boarding</ent>⟦br⟧
